      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Testing a dose change on your own is medically unsound, no matter how stable you feel. The danger in lowering the dose prematurely is an increased risk of dangerous blood clots, which is what warfarin is meant to prevent. Please contact your healthcare provider's office immediately to see if they offer a quick telehealth consultation to discuss your dosage needs.",
      "source": "target",
